---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - MIDI Volume Control - Field Bureau + Werkstatt"
  description="Terms of Service for MIDI Volume Control app"
  gradientOverlay="linear-gradient(to bottom, #4a4a4a, #2a2a2a)"
>
  <div class="relative min-h-screen flex flex-col">

    <!-- Breadcrumb Navigation -->
    <nav class="relative z-10 px-6 md:px-12 py-6">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-white/80 drop-shadow-lg">
        <a href="/midi-volume" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">MIDI Volume Control</a>
        <span class="text-white/40">/</span>
        <span class="text-white">Terms of Service</span>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 px-6 md:px-12 py-12 flex-1">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="text-center mb-16 animate-fade-in-up" style="opacity: 0;">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-light text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
            Terms of Service
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-white/70 drop-shadow-lg">
            MIDI Volume Control
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 mt-4 drop-shadow-lg">
            Last updated: September 1, 2025
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Content Sections -->
        <div class="space-y-8 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 200ms; opacity: 0;">

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              By downloading, installing, or using MIDI Volume Control ("the App"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the App.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">2. Description of Service</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              MIDI Volume Control is a macOS application that allows users to control system volume and Apple Music volume using MIDI controllers. The App provides:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>System volume control via MIDI input</li>
              <li>Optional Apple Music volume control</li>
              <li>MIDI Learn functionality for controller mapping</li>
              <li>Menu bar integration</li>
              <li>Automatic device detection</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">3. System Requirements</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App requires:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>macOS 10.15 (Catalina) or later</li>
              <li>A MIDI controller or interface</li>
              <li>Apple Music app (for optional Apple Music control features)</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">4. Privacy and Data</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App operates with minimal data collection:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>MIDI device information is processed locally for controller mapping</li>
              <li>No personal data is transmitted to external servers</li>
              <li>Apple Music integration requires automation permission when enabled</li>
              <li>All settings and configurations are stored locally on your device</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">5. Permissions</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App may request the following permissions:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li><strong>MIDI Access:</strong> Required for receiving MIDI controller input</li>
              <li><strong>Apple Music Automation:</strong> Optional permission for controlling Apple Music volume</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mt-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              You can revoke these permissions at any time through macOS System Preferences.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We are not liable for any damages arising from the use of the App, including but not limited to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>Hardware compatibility issues</li>
              <li>MIDI controller malfunctions</li>
              <li>System audio interruptions</li>
              <li>Data loss or corruption</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">7. User Responsibilities</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              Users are responsible for:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>Ensuring MIDI controller compatibility</li>
              <li>Proper configuration of MIDI devices</li>
              <li>Backing up system preferences if desired</li>
              <li>Using the App in accordance with these Terms</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">8. Updates and Changes</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              We may update the App and these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the App after updates constitutes acceptance of any changes. Major updates will be distributed through the Mac App Store.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">9. Termination</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              You may stop using the App at any time by uninstalling it from your device. These Terms will remain in effect until terminated by either party.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="border border-white/20 rounded-xl p-8 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/5">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">10. Contact Information</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              If you have questions about these Terms or the App, please contact us through the Mac App Store.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="border border-white/30 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/10">
            <p class="text-sm text-white/70 drop-shadow-lg">
              These Terms of Service are effective as of September 1, 2025. By using MIDI Volume Control, you acknowledge that you have read and understood these Terms and agree to be bound by them.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer with black background -->
  <footer class="bg-black py-8 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-center text-white/30 text-xs tracking-wide">
        <span class="font-semibold">Field Bureau + Werkstatt</span>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        © {new Date().getFullYear()} Field Bureau & Werkstatt LLC. All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
